# Chess Online - Project Overview

Real-time multiplayer chess app with a Node.js/TypeScript server and React client.

## Architecture

- **`server/`** — Express + Socket.IO + Mongoose + chess.js
  - `src/models/Room.ts` — Mongoose schema for game rooms (state, clocks, players)
  - `src/game/GameManager.ts` — Core game logic: room lifecycle, move validation via chess.js, timers
  - `src/socket/handlers.ts` — Socket.IO event handlers wiring client events to GameManager
  - `src/index.ts` — Express server entry point, serves built client as static files
- **`client/`** — React + Vite + react-chessboard v5 + Socket.IO client
  - `src/App.tsx` — Root routing: name prompt → lobby → game room, handles reconnection
  - `src/components/Lobby.tsx` — Room list and creation form
  - `src/components/GameRoom.tsx` — Chessboard, clocks, move list, resign
  - `src/socket.ts` — Singleton Socket.IO client instance
- **`Dockerfile`** — Multi-stage build (client build → server build → production image)
- **`docker-compose.yml`** — App + MongoDB

## Key Patterns

- Game state is the source of truth in MongoDB; chess.js instances are kept in-memory for fast validation
- Timers are server-side `setInterval` keyed by roomId, not tied to sockets
- Client persists `roomId` + `playerName` in localStorage for reconnection
- react-chessboard v5 uses `options` prop (not top-level props)
